{
  "stem": "7739.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Made them go through this disinfection again, isolation or quarantine, and then they sent them away-- didn't know where.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My father and I, with the rest of the people, I think, or most of the people, were transferred to the next adjoining camp, called D Camp.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was assigned a barrack together with my father.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Then I was separated from my father to a different barrack because I worked in a different place where he worked.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We were assigned work.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I think at that time he worked in a place where they had a big warehouse where they used to bring in airplanes that are shot down for dismantling and salvaging of parts of the airplanes.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then we had different jobs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So my father and I didn't have-- since we didn't work on the same job, we were assigned different barracks.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Then, I think it was late in November or-- that they picked my father together with another group.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You get used to the life of the camp, and you could see what was taking place already, to be sent away somewhere.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I know that he was again quarantined in a-- in a-- in a barrack, and you couldn't get near there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But I knew eventually that they would have to come out of the camp, go through the outside of the perimeter of the camp, between which was a road leading to the railway, where we came in.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That-- that's where they will lead them out, and I was waiting every day.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And finally, I waited till they were taking them out.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
